Cool Graph Function

pwilliams

3/4/2019

Want to see a cool graphing function?

First, download the dataset:

df = read.csv("./mushroom_growth.csv")
head(df, n = 10)
##        Species Light Nitrogen Humidity Temperature GrowthRate
## 1  P.ostreotus     0        0      Low          20     23.924
## 2  P.ostreotus    10        0      Low          20     34.132
## 3  P.ostreotus    20        0      Low          20    134.782
## 4  P.ostreotus     0        5      Low          20     44.516
## 5  P.ostreotus    10        5      Low          20     44.252
## 6  P.ostreotus    20        5      Low          20     81.080
## 7  P.ostreotus     0       10      Low          20     31.844
## 8  P.ostreotus    10       10      Low          20     53.624
## 9  P.ostreotus    20       10      Low          20    167.628
## 10 P.ostreotus     0       20      Low          20    109.416

Once the data set is loaded in and you want to start testing the relationship between variables to get a feel for the data, you can run the function ggpairs (from the GGallly package):

ggpairs(df)

How sweet is that?
